-- Nihon Unisys Says It Had 5.6 Billion Yen Invested in AIJ
-- B y   C h r i s   C o o p e r   a n d   T a k a k o   T a n i g u c h i
-- 2012-02-29T11:12:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/nihon-unisys-says-it-had-5-6-billion-yen-invested-in-aij.html
Nihon Unisys Ltd. (8056) , a Japanese
software company, said it had 5.6 billion yen ($70 million), or
6.6 percent of its pension-fund assets, invested in AIJ
Investment Advisors Co.  Tokyo-based Nihon Unisys made the announcement in a
statement to the Tokyo Stock Exchange.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Chris Cooper in Tokyo at 
 ccooper1@bloomberg.net ;
Takako Taniguchi in Tokyo at 
 ttaniguchi4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
